name: Kenmore Air Harbor, LLC.
about: Kenmore Air Harbor, LLC, is a renowned flying school and seaplane operation based at the northern end of Lake Washington, Washington. Since its inception in 1946 by founders Bob Munro, Reg Collins, and Jack Mines, the company has grown into one of the most respected seaplane operations globally. With a fleet of 25 aircraft, including de Havilland Beavers, Otters, Cessna Caravans, and the Pilatus PC-12, Kenmore Air offers initial and advanced flight training in some of the world's most popular and proven seaplanes. The school utilizes aircraft such as the Piper SuperCub, Cessna 172, and the legendary de Havilland Beaver. Known for its exceptional aircraft maintenance and restoration services, Kenmore Air Harbor ensures top-notch training and safety standards. With a rich history and a commitment to customer needs, Kenmore Air Harbor continues to be the leader in seaplane operations and flight instruction.
